Stage 1 — Foundations (1–2 months)

Goal: Build strong fundamentals in math, programming, and data handling.

1. Math Essentials

Statistics: distributions, probability, hypothesis testing

Linear algebra: vectors, matrices

Calculus basics: derivatives, gradients

2. Python Fundamentals

Python basics: variables, loops, functions

NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib

Clean coding practices

Git & GitHub version control

3. Starter Projects

Exploratory data analysis on Kaggle datasets

Data cleaning and visualization

Simple descriptive statistics reports

Checkpoint

Comfortable with Python and data manipulation

Able to analyze and visualize datasets

Stage 2 — Core Machine Learning (2–3 months)

Goal: Learn classic ML algorithms and evaluation methods.

4. Supervised Learning

Linear regression

Logistic regression

Decision trees

Random forests

Gradient boosting (XGBoost, LightGBM)

5. Model Evaluation

Train/validation/test split

Cross-validation

Precision, recall, F1-score

Confusion matrix

ROC/AUC

6. Unsupervised Learning

KMeans

PCA

DBSCAN

Anomaly detection basics

Projects

House price prediction

Customer churn classification

Customer segmentation

Sales/demand prediction

Checkpoint

Able to build and evaluate ML models

Can explain performance metrics

Stage 3 — Deep Learning and NLP (2–3 months)

Goal: Learn modern AI techniques.

7. Deep Learning

PyTorch or TensorFlow

Feedforward neural networks

Convolutional neural networks (CNNs)

Recurrent networks (LSTM/GRU)

8. Natural Language Processing (NLP)

Tokenization, TF-IDF

Word embeddings

Transformer models (BERT, DistilBERT)

Text classification and sentiment analysis

Projects

Sentiment analysis

Image classifier

Product review classifier

Simple chatbot

Checkpoint

Able to train deep learning models

Understand transformer fine-tuning basics

Stage 4 — Data Engineering and MLOps (2–4 months)

Goal: Learn how to deploy and scale real data science systems.

9. Data Engineering

SQL (MySQL or PostgreSQL)

Data pipelines (Airflow or Prefect)

Cloud basics (AWS, GCP, or Azure)

Building APIs (FastAPI or Flask)

10. MLOps

Model deployment techniques

Docker and containers

MLflow for experiment tracking

Monitoring and model drift

CI/CD basics (GitHub Actions)

Projects

ETL pipeline

Deployed ML model via API

Automated daily workflow

Interactive dashboard

Checkpoint

Can deploy a model in a simple production environment

Stage 5 — Choose a Specialization

Once you have the core skills, choose one or two tracks:

A. NLP Specialist

RAG systems

Vector databases

LLM fine-tuning

Chatbot systems

B. Machine Learning Engineer

Distributed training

Model optimization

High-performance serving

C. Business/Data Science Focus

A/B testing

Causal inference

Forecasting

Business storytelling

D. Analytics/BI

Tableau or Power BI

Dashboard design

KPI reporting

Recommended Resources

Free

Kaggle micro-courses

Fast.ai

Google ML Crash Course

YouTube: StatQuest, 3Blue1Brown

Paid

Coursera: Andrew Ng Machine Learning

Coursera: Deep Learning Specialization

Udemy: Python for Data Science / ML Bootcamps
